com.spectralogic.ds3client

Class Ds3Client

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.spectralogic.ds3client.Ds3Client

  • public class Ds3Client
extends java.lang.Object
    The main class for communicating with a DS3 appliance. All communication with a DS3 appliance should start with this class. Here is an example showing how the Ds3Client class is used to get a list of buckets from a remote DS3 appliance. 
         final Ds3Client client = Ds3Client.builder("ds3Endpoint:8080",
                                  new Credentials("accessKey", "secretKey")).build();

     final GetServiceResponse response = client.getService(new GetServiceRequest());

     for(final Bucket bucket: response.getResult().getBuckets()) {
         System.out.println(bucket.getName());
     }

        Primes the Ds3 appliance for a Bulk Get. This does not perform the gets for each individual files. See getObject(GetObjectRequest) for performing the get.
        Parameters:
        request - The Bulk Get Request object used to customize the HTTP request. The bulk get request object has some options for customizing the request. See BulkGetRequest for the full list of options that can be configured.
        Returns:
        The response object contains a list of lists of files to get from the DS3 endpoint. Make sure that the files are gotten in the order specified in the response.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
        java.security.SignatureException
